This nest shows signs of much recent activity. Perhaps it is the nest of the brood's queen?

Disturbing it might produce the queen herself.

<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: This instance quest is meant to be run Solo and cannot be run in a group.</rgb>
'Indeed? You have fought and slain a mighty queen among the insect brood? This brings me great relief, though I know it is but a matter of time before they breed another.\n\n'Thank you!'
You prod at the nest, producing some unexpected results....\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: This instance quest is meant to be run Solo and cannot be run in a group.</rgb>

One of the nests among the insect burrows seems to bear signs of much activity. Perhaps this is the nest of the brood's queen?\n\n<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: This instance quest is meant to be run Solo and cannot be run in a group.</rgb>
Disturb the nest to draw forth the Queen of Queens

The queen's nest is at the insect-nest, north-east of the Woodman camp in the Rushgore.

Perhaps disturbing the nest will produce the brood's queen.

<rgb=#FF0000>NOTE: This instance quest is meant to be run Solo and cannot be run in a group.</rgb>
Talk to Gisalic at the Woodman camp in the Rushgore
Gisalic is at the Woodman camp in the Rushgore, south-west of the insect nest.\n\nGisalic will want to know that you have defeated the queen of the brood.
